======================================================================
PART 3: D^4 ALGEBRAIC STRUCTURE
======================================================================
D^4 deg-2 = T_pure + T_mixed
T_pure = sum_k 4*(S_a*S_b^3 + S_a^3*S_b)
T_mixed = sum_k 12*S_a*S_b*sum_{c!=a,b} S_c^2

CLAIM: T_mixed = -3 * T_pure
PROOF: sum_{c=1}^m S_c^2 = (p-1)/4  [half-angle identity]
  sum_{c!=a,b} S_c^2 = (p-1)/4 - S_a^2 - S_b^2
  T_mixed = 12*sum_k S_a*S_b*[(p-1)/4 - S_a^2 - S_b^2]
         = 3(p-1)*[D^2 deg-2] - 12*sum_k S_a*S_b*(S_a^2+S_b^2)
         = 3(p-1)*0 - 3*T_pure  [since D^2 deg-2 = 0]
  => D^4 deg-2 = T_pure - 3*T_pure = -2*T_pure

