    g(a) ~ 0 at p=1 mod 4! The sine Gauss sum vanishes.
    This means the product law sign(h_hat)=chi(ab) FAILS at p=1 mod 4.
    At p=1 mod 4, the degree-2 Walsh is controlled by COSINE sums instead.

